Limpopo police are investigating a case of culpable homicide following the death of three people on Gravelotte Road in Namakgale outside Phalaborwa on Saturday. According to Limpopo police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe, the  driver of a Toyota Etios sedan was travelling with his family to a wedding in Nkowankowa when he lost control of the vehicle and hit a tree. “During this accident, three occupants, twins, a boy and a girl Ossie and Ossly Sibuyi, aged five and 46-year-old Agnes Sibuyi died instantly while five others, including a driver were taken to hospital with serious injuries for medical attention,” Ngoepe said. Ngoepe said investigations are continuing. -TNA Reporter